description:
&lt;p&gt;First of all we are delighted you’re looking at this job opportunity and hope you want to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to join the prestigious ranks of the top 100 companies to work for in the UK-wide Best Companies Survey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Committed to the highest standards of care and excellence?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Looking to enhance or develop your skills to lead an award-winning team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Wanting to make a difference in a growing organisation and innovative culture?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Wanting to be continually supported in your chosen path of progression?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you enjoy a working environment where no two days are the same?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to make a difference the lives of residents with neurological conditions and their family and carers? &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you have the skills and enthusiasm to manage a team of very experienced Nurses and can provide high level clinical expertise to the team?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to make an impact in your Nursing career, then we are the organisation to do it with and we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PJ Care is one of the Sunday Times Top 100 Companies To Work For in 2019, and is a leading provider of specialist neurological care and neuro rehabilitation for people with progressive or acquired neurological conditions. We specialise in the multidisciplinary care of adults and work with residents, families, charities and the NHS to provide the highest quality care. Our residents are at the heart of everything we do and we strive to nurture dignity, independence and holistic wellbeing through the specialist care models, therapies and activities we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
